
   BACK ONLINE TONIGHT  

As Rod Stewart once said 'Do Ya think
I'm sexy'?
Or was it 'Tonights the night'?

Well anyway, the good news is the Main
Compunet System is up and working.

As I type this there are only a couple
of ports connected but we are working on
the rest as the day goes on.

BT have so far only connected 14 of the
16 available lines, but (being long
distance only) this shouldn't cause too
much trouble after the initial rush.

There may be a couple of facilities not
running over this first weekenend. These
include NETWHO and REALM. FED is running
and so is PartyLine.

Remember PLine is  HALF PRICE  until
further notice.
Subs are not being charged until June
(at least) and there is no Connect time
charge.

Finally. 2400 baud access is not
available at the moment. More news will
appear on the main system. If there are
any major problems I'll keep you
informed on this system.   THE DRAL 

